definitions.definition: a nocturnal bird of prey with large eyes, a facial disc, a hooked beak, and typically a loud hooting call.
definitions.example: I love reaching out into that absolute silence, when you can hear the owl or the wind.

definitions.definition: a woody perennial plant, typically having a single stem or trunk growing to a considerable height and bearing lateral branches at some distance from the ground.
a wooden structure or part of a structure.
a bound set of blank sheets for writing in.
definitions.example: an accounts book

definitions.definition: a set of tickets, stamps, matches, samples of cloth, etc., bound together.
definitions.example: a pattern book

definitions.definition: the first six tricks taken by the declarer in a hand of bridge, after which further tricks count towards fulfilling the contract.
reserve (accommodation, a place, etc.); buy (a ticket) in advance.
definitions.example: I have booked a table at the Swan

definitions.definition: make an official note of the personal details of (a person who has broken a law or rule).
definitions.example: the cop booked me and took me down to the station

definitions.definition: a written or printed work consisting of pages glued or sewn together along one side and bound in covers.
definitions.example: a book of selected poems

definitions.definition: used to refer to the person or people that the speaker is addressing.
definitions.example: are you listening?

definitions.definition: used to refer to any person in general.
definitions.example: after a while, you get used to it

definitions.definition: a mainly herbaceous plant with jointed stems and spikes of small wind-pollinated flowers, predominant in grass.
vegetation consisting of typically short plants with long, narrow leaves, growing wild or cultivated on lawns and pasture, and as a fodder crop.
definitions.example: he sat down on the grass

definitions.definition: a domesticated carnivorous mammal that typically has a long snout, an acute sense of smell, non-retractile claws, and a barking, howling, or whining voice.
definitions.example: she went for long walks with her dog

definitions.definition: a small domesticated carnivorous mammal with soft fur, a short snout, and retractile claws. It is widely kept as a pet or for catching mice, and many breeds have been developed.
definitions.example: their pet cat

definitions.definition: a warm-blooded egg-laying vertebrate animal distinguished by the possession of feathers, wings, a beak, and typically by being able to fly.
definitions.example: the valley is teeming with bird life

definitions.definition: a set of facts or figures systematically displayed, especially in columns.
definitions.example: the population has grown, as shown in table 1

definitions.definition: a piece of furniture with a flat top and one or more legs, providing a level surface for eating, writing, or working at.
definitions.example: she put the plate on the table

definitions.definition: a large area of water surrounded by land.
definitions.example: boys were swimming in the lake

definitions.definition: an insoluble pigment made by combining a soluble organic dye and an insoluble mordant.
any of the regular occasions in a day when a reasonably large amount of food is eaten.
definitions.example: the evening meal

definitions.definition: the edible part of any grain or pulse ground to powder.
definitions.example: she called to Judith to bring some meal for the hens

definitions.definition: a liquid dish, typically savoury and made by boiling meat, fish, or vegetables etc. in stock or water.
definitions.example: a bowl of tomato soup

definitions.definition: the air taken into or expelled from the lungs.
definitions.example: I was gasping for breath

definitions.definition: a hot drink made by infusing the dried crushed leaves of the tea plant in boiling water.
definitions.example: Katherine sipped her tea

definitions.definition: the action or fact of dying or being killed; the end of the life of a person or organism.
definitions.example: he had been depressed since the death of his father

definitions.definition: the fleshy muscular organ in the mouth of a mammal, used for tasting, licking, swallowing, and (in humans) articulating speech.
definitions.example: a galantine of tongue

definitions.definition: one's father.
definitions.example: his dad was with him

definitions.definition: a series of steps between floors or levels.
definitions.example: I climbed the three flights of stairs which led to his office

definitions.definition: an extravagant or far-fetched idea or thought process.
definitions.example: his research assistant was prone to flights of fancy

definitions.definition: a flock or large body of birds or insects in the air, especially when migrating.
definitions.example: flights of whooper swans

definitions.definition: the action of fleeing.
definitions.example: the enemy were now in flight

definitions.definition: the action or process of flying through the air.
definitions.example: an eagle in flight

definitions.definition: information or allegations regarded as damaging or scandalous.
definitions.example: the two sides took over the local media to throw mud at each other

definitions.definition: soft, sticky matter resulting from the mixing of earth and water.
definitions.example: ankle deep in mud, we squelched across a meadow
